        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:50PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 249 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 4 miles northeast of
Hermosa to 3 miles west of Cascade Falls. Movement was east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs, Edgemont, Hermosa, Keystone, Buffalo Gap, Pringle,
Fairburn, Hayward, Rockerville, Argyle, Wind Cave National Park,
Mount Rushmore National Memorial, Stockade Lake, Legion Lake,
Maverick Junction, Buffalo Corrals, State Game Lodge, Thompson Butte,
Angostura Reservoir, and Blue Bell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
